@node info "Information"
@toc main

                        Info
                        ----

Welcome to The Amiga CD-ROM Guide. This guide contains a full list of CD-ROMs
that are compatible with one of, or all of the Amiga computers. It gives
you details on each CD (if available). You will also find a list of 
publishers and their address. 

If you're looking for a particular CD, there are four ways to find it:

1. Click on it's name in the list of CDs. 
   @{" CD-ROMs " link CDALL }

2. Click on the publishers name in the list of publishers. 
   @{" Publishers " link PUBALL }

3. Click on a theme/keyword to get a list of CDs that assosiates with the
   theme/keyword.
   @{" Theme " link keywordALL } 

4. If you're not sure of the name, take a look in the @{"index" link index} where
   more names are added for each CD. Example: "Aminet 3" and "Aminet June 94" is
   the same CD.


If you find a bug, or see that the guide is incomplete, please contact @{"me" link AB}.
(See @{" Contribute " link contribute })
See @{"help" link help} for more help.

NB! I, Anders Bakkevold, do NOT sell the CD-ROMs in this guide. To buy 
    a CD-ROM, contact a CD-ROM @{"retailer" link DI-Select}.

@endnode
