@node Contribute "How to contribute."
@toc main

If you have any suggestions or have found any bugs, then contact @{"me" link AB}
immideately.

If you have more information on covered CDs, or about new CDs then 
contact @{"me" link AB} too. You will be credited in the guide.

I'm espesially seeking for people who have bought/tested a CD, and
who could write descriptive "contents" and "testers opinion".
If you have a different opinion than the tester in "testers opinion",
then feel free to write to me and tell me what you think.

And of course if you have any information which could fill the gap:
"@{i}Information not available.@{ui}" - then don't just sit there!

@endnode
