@node help  
@toc main

@{b}Name.............@{ub} The name of the CD-ROM
@{b}Publisher........@{ub} The publisher of the CD-ROM
@{b}Price............@{ub} The Price of the CD-ROM. This is only to give you
                  a hunch of how much it costs. Prices may vary.
@{b}CDROMs...........@{ub} How many CD-ROM discs??
@{b}Used Space.......@{ub} How much of the CD-ROM is used in Megabytes.
@{b}Language.........@{ub} The main language (Mostly English or Deutsch)
@{b}Bootable.........@{ub} Can you boot from the CD-ROM?
                  For unexpanded CD32's it is essential that the CD-ROM
                  boots!!
@{b}Filesystem.......@{ub} The file-system. 
                  ISO9660 / ISO9660-1  : Standard format (8.3) 
                  ISO9660-2 : Allows longer filenames etc

@{b}Requirements.....@{ub} What do you need to use the software? Not so
                  essential requierments in brackets (). 
@{b}Usable Software..@{ub} 

                  How much of the software is compatible with a
                  platform (approx.). This information is based on
                  guessing, and may not be correct. It only gives
                  you an idea of how useful it is for a platform.
                  
@{b}Release Date.....@{ub} The date of the release. This shows you if the
                  CD-ROM is very old. 
                    
@{b}Contents.........@{ub} The contents of the CD-ROM.

@{b}Access Software..@{ub} Any software included for accessing the software
                  on the cd-rom. EG Index-files, search utilities etc.
                  "None" means that no accesss software is included.

@{b}Comments.........@{ub} Anything special about the CD-ROM.  
                  Might be the ISBN number.

@{b}Testers Opinion..@{ub} The opinion of a person who has tested the
                  CD-ROM. This information is subjective. It is 
                  signed by the person who has tested the CD-ROM.
                  You may also find quotes from magazine's reviews.

@{b}Keywords.........@{ub} Keywords that assosiate with the contents of the
                  CD-ROM. Used in the @{" Theme " link keywordALL } node.

@{b}Sources..........@{ub} The contributers to the above information.

@endnode
